cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with security techniques in wireless communication systems, specifically in the physical layer. It focuses on pilot contamination attacks and proposes a solution to detect them. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the security aspect of the proposed solution, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with wireless communication systems, which could be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed solution numerically, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
